{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01TRtHRaoH2khgKBdrcdLXfL","type":"tool_result","content":"=== agent-eval-harness.md ===\n# Agent Eval Harness\n\nA framework for evaluating AI agent skill quality through automated testing, judge scoring, and iterative optimization.\n\n=== ai-first-sync-2026-06-25.md ===\n# AI-First Sync -- June 25, 2026\n\nRed Hat AI UXD AI-First Sync. Evan's prototype evaluator presentation and 3.6 branch strategy.\n\n=== ai-sdlc-pipeline.md ===\n# AI-SDLC Pipeline\n\nRed Hat's AI-assisted Software Development Life Cycle — a three-phase pipeline where each phase has its own \"creator\" tool.\n\n=== andy-evan-2026-06-22.md ===\n# Andy/Evan Meeting -- June 22, 2026\n\n1:1 review of evaluation system progress and prototype creator integration strategy.\n\n=== andy-evan-2026-06-29.md ===\n# Andy/Evan Meeting -- June 29, 2026\n\n1:1 covering prototype evaluator progress, reporting infrastructure, repository strategy, and future directions.\n\n=== andy-evan-eval-review-2026-06-16.md ===\n# Andy/Evan Evaluation Review — June 16, 2026\n\nMeeting with Andy Braren reviewing the prototype evaluation system. Three key decisions shaped the direction of the evaluator super agent.\n\n=== ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md ===\n# Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17\n\nStrategy session on integrating the UXD AI Helpers repo with Ansible's Carbonite harness. First major external consumer of the centralized skill distribution model.\n\n=== cursor-work-2026-06-16.md ===\n# Cursor Agent Work — June 16, 2026\n\nA daily record of all agent work done across 4 Cursor sessions on this date. Focused on productivity infrastructure: skills that make other skills better, zero-friction workflows, and manager-oriented accountability.\n\n=== decision-kit.md ===\n# Decision Kit\n\nA toolkit for Decision Driven Development. AI does the busywork around your decisions — you make the calls.\n\n=== evaluator-super-agent.md ===\n# Evaluator Super Agent\n\nEvan's primary assignment: build an evaluation agent that automates prototype quality assessment within the [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) pipeline.\n\n=== index.md ===\n# Wiki Index\n\nA catalog of all wiki pages, organized by category.\n\n=== log.md ===\n# Change Log\n\nA chronological record of all wiki operations.\n\n=== midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md ===\n# Midpoint Check-in with Zack -- June 30, 2026\n\nHalfway internship check-in focused on growth, energy management, strengths/opportunities feedback, and career direction. Not a work-progress meeting.\n\n=== my-cursor-claw.md ===\n# My Cursor Claw\n\nPersonal skill development workspace built during the Day of Learning Agent Skills Workshop (2026-06-05). Contains 20+ custom Cursor skills, 5 MCP server connections, and automated daily review infrastructure.\n\n=== nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md ===\n# Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge\n\nFirst hands-on internship assignment: apply Nielsen Norman's 10 Usability Heuristics to Kubernetes-style interfaces across multiple AI tools and compare their analysis quality.\n\n=== outcome-tiger-team.md ===\n# Outcome Tiger Team\n\nProposal by Andy Braren to form a cross-functional tiger team focused on the critical step *before* the [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md): creating, prioritizing, and visualizing **outcomes** — the directional goals that determine which features get prioritized and why.\n\n=== prototype-creator-demo-may14.md ===\n# Prototype Creator Demo — May 14, 2026\n\nAndy Braren's recorded walkthrough of prototype-creator for the team, with Beau Morley and Dash Copeland participating. Demonstrates both automated and human-in-the-loop workflows end-to-end.\n\n=== prototype-creator.md ===\n# Prototype Creator\n\nPhase 2 (\"the SHOW\") of Red Hat's [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md). Takes RFE user stories and produces rapid prototypes that make the proposed experience tangible before engineering commits.\n\n=== redhat-ai-first-lessons.md ===\n# Red Hat AI-First Lessons\n\nJeremy Eder's (Distinguished Engineer, 16 years at Red Hat) presentation on lessons from Red Hat Engineering on AI-first software development. 38-slide deck covering the agentic SDLC, issue-to-PR bots, evaluation infrastructure, and organizational change.\n\n=== retrieval-augmented-generation.md ===\n# Retrieval-Augmented Generation\n\nRetrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is a technique that enhances LLM responses by retrieving relevant documents from an external knowledge base before generating an answer. Instead of relying solely on the model's training data, RAG grounds responses in real, up-to-date documents.\n\n=== rfe-creator.md ===\n# RFE Creator\n\nPhase 1 (\"the WHAT\") of Red Hat's [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md). Claude Code skills for creating, reviewing, and submitting RFEs (Requests for Enhancement) to the RHAIRFE Jira project.\n\n=== rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-18.md ===\n# RH AI-First UX — 2026-06-18\n\nWeekly team meeting for the Red Hat AI-first UX team. Key theme: **tool evaluation, prototype infrastructure unlocks, and formalizing project management structure**.\n\n=== rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-25.md ===\n# RH AI-First UX -- June 25, 2026\n\nWeekly AI-first UX team meeting covering Outcome Creator, testing strategy, and infrastructure alignment.\n\n=== session-log-2026-06-15.md ===\n# Session Log — 2026-06-15\n\n**Tags:** #daily-log #2026-06-15 #skills #canvas #second-brain #prototype-creator\n\n=== session-log-2026-06-16.md ===\n# Session Log — 2026-06-16\n\n**Signal:** 2 important items, 0 stale carry-forwards\n\n=== skill-overlays.md ===\n# Skill Overlays\n\nLLM-generated, project-specific context files that sit on top of general-purpose skills. Instead of re-inferring a project's structure on every run, you pre-generate a dense context layer capturing architecture, naming conventions, patterns, and implicit standards.\n\n=== standup-2026-06-22.md ===\n# Standup -- June 22, 2026\n\nTeam standup for Future Sustainability & E2E. Sprint capacity adjustments and customer engagement strategy.\n\n=== standup-2026-06-29.md ===\n# Standup -- June 29, 2026\n\nTeam standup for Future Sustainability & E2E. Usability testing updates, UX debt prioritization, and research tooling.\n\n=== ux-quality-rubric.md ===\n# UX Quality Rubric\n\nThe scoring system used by [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) to evaluate generated prototypes. Scored by a restricted `prototype-scorer` agent (no shell, no network, no MCP).\n\n=== vector-databases.md ===\n# Vector Databases\n\nA vector database stores data as high-dimensional vectors (embeddings) and enables fast similarity search. They are a key component in [RAG](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) pipelines, recommendation systems, and semantic search.\n\n=== vector-similarity-search.md ===\n# Vector Similarity Search\n\nCore technique for finding semantically similar content using vector embeddings — the engine behind modern search, recommendations, and deduplication.\n\n=== weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md ===\n# Weekly Design Sync — July 1, 2026\n\nMeeting with Andy Braren, Evan Jaquez, and Zack Bodnar covering evaluator demo prep, PatternFly 6 migration, and rubric methodology.\n\n=== wg-uxd-efficiency-2026-06-29.md ===\n# WG: UXD Efficiency & AI Enablement -- June 29, 2026\n\nWorking group meeting on AI helpers repository strategy, productivity skills, and cost management.\n\n=== zack-evan-2026-06-24.md ===\n# Zack/Evan Meeting -- June 24, 2026\n\n1:1 covering Jira standardization, sprint planning methodology, and AI skill architecture strategy.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fd38bce-a9ae-438a-9881-c43de165fe03","uuid":"b0bec396-4b43-4f66-ac52-ba958de17b5b","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:39:00.737Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"=== agent-eval-harness.md ===\n# Agent Eval Harness\n\nA framework for evaluating AI agent skill quality through automated testing, judge scoring, and 