{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01KYpRVMkP5c74hufggpWi4g","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Skill Overlays\n2\t\n3\tLLM-generated, project-specific context files that sit on top of general-purpose skills. Instead of re-inferring a project's structure on every run, you pre-generate a dense context layer capturing architecture, naming conventions, patterns, and implicit standards.\n4\t\n5\t## Key Concepts\n6\t\n7\t- An LLM analyzes project metadata (source code, git history, schemas, config files)\n8\t- Generates context files capturing the project's implicit guidelines and conventions\n9\t- Overlay files sit alongside general-purpose skills and provide project-specific grounding\n10\t- The agent loads the overlay as part of its context when working on that project\n11\t- Pattern is language/framework/domain agnostic\n12\t\n13\t## Concrete Example\n14\t\n15\tIn the data products ADLC (Carl Trieloff's org), an MCP server connects to Snowflake and reads metadata for all data products. An LLM generates skill files (one per data product) with specific context about structure, lineage, and naming conventions. Before overlays, the agent was \"assuming certain things\" and making inference errors. After adding overlays, implementation quality \"went drastically cleaner.\"\n16\t\n17\t## Open Questions\n18\t\n19\t- **Dynamic vs. static:** Runtime generation via MCP avoids staleness but adds latency/cost. Checked-in files are fast but drift.\n20\t- **Scale:** How to generate and maintain overlays across hundreds of repos?\n21\t- **Freshness:** How to detect when an overlay is stale enough to regenerate?\n22\t\n23\t## Who Validated It\n24\t\n25\t- Carl Trieloff / Nathan Chandirasegarane's team (data products ADLC). Concept invented Apr 4, 2026, first tested Apr 7.\n26\t- UIE adopting the pattern for harness engineering work.\n27\t\n28\t## Related\n29\t\n30\t- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) -- overlays are relevant to the team-specific overlay approach for prototype evaluation\n31\t- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) -- overlays improve agent accuracy, directly relevant to eval quality\n32\t- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) -- the claw already uses project-specific context (skills, rules), overlays formalize this pattern\n33\t- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) -- overlays plug into the pipeline as a context engineering technique\n34\t\n35\t## Sources\n36\t\n37\t- ~/Desktop/Second Brain Inbox/skill-overlays.md\n38\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fd38bce-a9ae-438a-9881-c43de165fe03","uuid":"0e0598e8-d8f7-4d06-a9c5-2a00212cf81d","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:39:24.747Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/skill-overlays.md","content":"# Skill Overlays\n\nLLM-generated, project-specific context files that sit on top of general-purpose skills. Instead of re-inferring a project's structure on every run, you pre-generate a dense context layer capturing architecture, naming conventions, patterns, and implicit standards.\n\n## Key Concepts\n\n- An LLM analyzes project metadata (source code, git history, schemas, config files)\n- Generates context files capturing the project's implicit guidelines and conventions\n- Overlay files sit alongside general-purpose skills and provide project-specific grounding\n- The agent loads the overlay as part of its context when working on that project\n- Pattern is language/framework/domain agnostic\n\n## Concrete Example\n\nIn the data products ADLC (Carl Trieloff's org), an MCP server connects to Snowflake and reads metadata for all data products. An LLM generates skill files (one per data product) with specific context about structure, lineage, and naming conventions. Before overlays, the agent was \"assuming certain things\" and making inference errors. After adding overlays, implementation quality \"went drastically cleaner.\"\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- **Dynamic vs. static:** Runtime generation via MCP avoids staleness but adds latency/cost. Checked-in files are fast but drift.\n- **Scale:** How to generate and maintain overlays across hundreds of repos?\n- **Freshness:** How to detect when an overlay is stale enough to regenerate?\n\n## Who Validated It\n\n- Carl Trieloff / Nathan Chandirasegarane's team (data products ADLC). Concept invented Apr 4, 2026, first tested Apr 7.\n- UIE adopting the pattern for harness engineering work.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) -- overlays are relevant to the team-specific overlay approach for prototype evaluation\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) -- overlays improve agent accuracy, directly relevant to eval quality\n- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) -- the claw already uses project-specific context (skills, rules), overlays formalize this pattern\n- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) -- overlays plug into the pipeline as a context engineering technique\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/Desktop/Second Brain Inbox/skill-overlays.md\n","numLines":38,"startLine":1,"totalLines":38}}}
