{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_014AA1EKfqhBKGA593AyhZ4C", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_018vq35MgjjPRF1mqT2TJ7gm", "name": "Write", "input": {"file_path": "/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/prompt-engineering-best-practices.md", "content": "# Prompt Engineering Best Practices\n\nCore techniques for writing effective LLM prompts that produce consistent, high-quality outputs.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- **Specify output format explicitly** \u2014 tell the model what structure you expect (JSON, bullets, table, prose) rather than inferring it\n- **Provide examples of good and bad output** \u2014 few-shot examples anchor the model more reliably than descriptions alone\n- **Use chain-of-thought for complex reasoning** \u2014 instruct the model to reason step-by-step before answering; improves accuracy on multi-hop problems\n- **Break multi-step tasks into sequential prompts** \u2014 a pipeline of focused prompts outperforms one sprawling mega-prompt\n- **Include constraints and boundaries explicitly** \u2014 state what the model should NOT do as clearly as what it should\n\n## Related\n\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) \u2014 judge prompts are the core of the eval harness; format specs and CoT directly improve scoring accuracy\n- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) \u2014 overlays are structured prompts with explicit constraints and project-specific examples baked in\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) \u2014 each evaluation phase uses format-controlled output and sequential prompting across phases\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/second-brain/sources/2026-06-15-prompt-engineering-best-practices.md\n- Ingested: 2026-07-09\n"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 764, "cache_read_input_tokens": 45173, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 764, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 21}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "4fd38bce-a9ae-438a-9881-c43de165fe03", "uuid": "fba12d7b-6bb8-43cf-b111-77281ca3bfde", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcrjbEX5rnketfQ68Yirz", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:39:47.848Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_018vq35MgjjPRF1mqT2TJ7gm","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/prompt-engineering-best-practices.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fd38bce-a9ae-438a-9881-c43de165fe03","uuid":"5ee43d91-0917-48c8-a4b0-0b9dcfc1b94c","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:39:47.853Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/prompt-engineering-best-practices.md","content":"# Prompt Engineering Best Practices\n\nCore techniques for writing effective LLM prompts that produce consistent, high-quality outputs.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- **Specify output format explicitly** — tell the model what structure you expect (JSON, bullets, table, prose) rather than inferring it\n- **Provide examples of good and bad output** — few-shot examples anchor the model more reliably than descriptions alone\n- **Use chain-of-thought for complex reasoning** — instruct the model to reason step-by-step before answering; improves accuracy on multi-hop problems\n- **Break multi-step tasks into sequential prompts** — a pipeline of focused prompts outperforms one sprawling mega-prompt\n- **Include constraints and boundaries explicitly** — state what the model should NOT do as clearly as what it should\n\n## Related\n\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — judge prompts are the core of the eval harness; format specs and CoT directly improve scoring accuracy\n- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — overlays are structured prompts with explicit constraints and project-specific examples baked in\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — each evaluation phase uses format-controlled output and sequential prompting across phases\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/second-brain/sources/2026-06-15-prompt-engineering-best-practices.md\n- Ingested: 2026-07-09\n","structuredPatch":[],"o