{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_019yht2gZSCCqY4F6BoyVNhs","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/agent-eval-harness.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fd38bce-a9ae-438a-9881-c43de165fe03","uuid":"d419176a-7853-4515-849b-08aca47149b6","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:39:53.197Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/agent-eval-harness.md","oldString":"- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — overlays improve agent accuracy, directly relevant to eval quality\n- [WG: UXD Efficiency — June 29](wg-uxd-efficiency-2026-06-29.md) — token efficiency and cost management for eval runs","newString":"- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — overlays improve agent accuracy, directly relevant to eval quality\n- [Prompt Engineering Best Practices](prompt-engineering-best-practices.md) — judge prompts and SKILL.md are prompt engineering artifacts; format specs and CoT improve scoring reliability\n- [WG: UXD Efficiency — June 29](wg-uxd-efficiency-2026-06-29.md) — token efficiency and cost management for eval runs","originalFile":"# Agent Eval Harness\n\nA framework for evaluating AI agent skill quality through automated testing, judge scoring, and iterative optimization.\n\n## How It Works\n\n1. **eval.yaml** — defines execution mode, dataset schema, output descriptions, judges, models, and thresholds\n2. **Dataset** — test cases with realistic inputs for the skill\n3. **Judges** — automated scorers that rate skill outputs against criteria\n4. **Run** — executes the skill against test cases, scores with judges, reports results\n5. **Optimize** — identifies failures, edits SKILL.md, re-runs to verify, checks for regressions\n\n## Key Skills (from the harness)\n\n- `/eval-analyze` — examine a skill and generate eval.yaml\n- `/eval-dataset` — generate test cases for a skill\n- `/eval-run` — execute evaluation against test cases\n- `/eval-optimize` — automated improvement loop\n- `/eval-review` — interactive human review of results\n\n## The Optimize Loop\n\n```\nRun eval → Identify judge failures → Read traces → Edit SKILL.md → Re-run → Verify\n```\n\nThis is directly applicable to the [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) work — the same pattern of rubric-based scoring, automated iteration, and quality gates.\n\n## MLflow Integration\n\nResults can be logged to MLflow for tracking, dataset syncing, and trace-level feedback.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — uses rubric-based scoring for prototypes\n- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — the 4-dimension scoring system\n- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) — includes run-evals skill\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — applies eval patterns to prototype evaluation\n- [Red Hat AI-First Lessons](redhat-ai-first-lessons.md) — Jeremy Eder's presentation referencing EvalHub, Harbor, MLflow, and the harness\n- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — eval patterns relevant to measuring heuristic eval pilot results\n- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — overlays improve agent accuracy, directly relevant to eval quality\n- [WG: UXD Efficiency — June 29](wg-uxd-efficiency-2026-06-29.md) — token efficiency and cost management for eval runs\n\n## Sources\n\n- sources/2026-06-04-agent-eval-harness-overview.html\n- opendatahub-io agent-eval-harness skills (installed as plugins)\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":39,"oldLines":6,"newStart":39,"newLines":7,"lines":[" - [Red Hat AI-First Lessons](redhat-ai-first-lessons.md) — Jeremy Eder's presentation referencing EvalHub, Harbor, MLflow, and the harness"," - [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — eval patterns relevant to measuring heuristic eval pilot results"," - [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — overlays improve agent accuracy, directly relevant to eval quality","+- [Prompt Engineering Best Practices](prompt-engineering-best-practices.md) — judge prompts and SKILL.md are prompt engineering artifacts; format specs and CoT improve scoring reliability"," - [WG: UXD Efficiency — June 29](wg-uxd-efficiency-2026-06-29.md) — token efficiency and cost management for eval runs"," "," ## Sources"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01KFkegEpo4q3cX9hXLPZvwg", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_011BnBW64NKRZd3VNuK8iQXb", "name": "Edit", "input": {"replace_all": false, "file_path": "/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/skill-overlays.md", "old_string": "- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) -- overlays plug into the pipeline as a context engineering technique", "new_string": "- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) -- overlays plug into the pipeline as a context engineering technique\n- [Prompt Engineering Best Practices](prompt-engineering-best-practices.md) \u2014 overlays are structured prompts; best practices for format, examples, and constraints apply directly"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 510, "cache_read_input_tokens": 45937, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 510, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "4fd38bce-a9ae-438a-9881-c43de165fe03", "uuid": "8496c844-673f-45a6-ba82-15697f9246ca", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcrjbqKqnV4imdJpcgxU4", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:39:55.681Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_011BnBW64NKRZd3VNuK8iQXb","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/skill-overlays.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fd38bce-a9ae-438a-9881-c43de165fe03","uuid":"7b317c39-d8a8-4a86-9071-67a9521a0cf7","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:39:55.688Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/skill-overlays.md","oldString":"- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) -- overlays plug into the pipeline as a context engineering technique","newString":"- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) -- overlays plug into the pipeline as a context engineering technique\n- [Prompt Engineering Best Practices](prompt-engineering-best-practices.md) — overlays are structured prompts; best practices for format, examples, and constraints apply directly","originalFile":"# Skill Overlays\n\nLLM-generated, project-specific context files that sit on top of general-purpose skills. Instead of re-inferring a project's structure on every run, you pre-generate a dense context layer capturing architecture, naming conventions, patterns, and implicit standards.\n\n## Key Concepts\n\n- An LLM analyzes project metadata (source code, git history, schemas, config files)\n- Generates context files capturing the project's implicit guidelines and conventions\n- Overlay files sit alongside general-purpose skills and provide project-specific grounding\n- The agent loads the overlay as part of its context when working on that project\n- Pattern is language/framework/domain agnostic\n\n## Concrete Example\n\nIn the data products ADLC (Carl Trieloff's org), an MCP server connects to Snowflake and reads metadata for all data products. An LLM generates skill files (one per data product) with specific context about structure, lineage, and naming conventions. Before overlays, the agent was \"assuming certain things\" and making inference errors. After adding overlays, implementation quality \"went drastically cleaner.\"\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- **Dynamic vs. static:** Runtime generation via MCP avoids staleness but adds latency/cost. Checked-in files are fast but drift.\n- **Scale:** How to generate and maintain overlays across hundreds of repos?\n- **Freshness:** How to detect when an overlay is stale enough to regenerate?\n\n## Who Validated It\n\n- Carl Trieloff / Nathan Chandirasegarane's team (data products ADLC). Concept invented Apr 4, 2026, first tested Apr 7.\n- UIE adopting the pattern for harness engineering work.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) -- overlays are relevant to the team-specific overlay approach for prototype evaluation\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) -- overlays improve agent accuracy, directly relevant to eval quality\n- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) -- the claw already uses project-specific context (skills, rules), overlays formalize this pattern\n- [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) -- overlays plug into the pipeline as a context engineering technique\n\n## Sources\n\n- ~/Desktop/Second Brain Inbox/skill-overlays.md\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":31,"oldLines":6,"newStart":31,"newLines":7,"lines":[" - [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) -- overlays improve agent accuracy, directly relevant to eval quality"," - [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) -- the claw already uses project-specific context (skills, rules), overlays formalize this pattern"," - [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md) -- overlays plug into the pipeline as a context engineering technique","+- [Prompt Engineering Best Practices](prompt-engineering-best-practices.md) — overlays are structured prompts; best practices for format, examples, and constraints apply directly"," "," ## Sources"," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01KFkegEpo4q3cX9hXLPZvwg", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_018qas5NQHN9rFwycq72FoJN", "name": "Edit", "input": {"replace_all": false, "file_path": "/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/evaluator-super-agent.md", "old_string": "- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) \u2014 context engineering technique relevant to team-specific overlays", "new_string": "- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) \u2014 context engineering technique relevant to team-specific overlays\n- [Prompt Engineering Best Practices](prompt-engineering-best-practices.md) \u2014 sequential prompting and format-controlled output underpin the 3-phase evaluation pipeline"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 510, "cache_read_input_tokens": 45937, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 510, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 1}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "4fd38bce-a9ae-438a-9881-c43de165fe03", "uuid": "5ab88e0f-9c5d-461d-8fa4-d13e75263afd", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcrjbqKqnV4imdJpcgxU4", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:39:56.948Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_018qas5NQHN9rFwycq72FoJN","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/evaluator-super-agent.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fd38bce-a9ae-438a-9881-c43de165fe03","uuid":"ee78672f-479a-43c8-b641-83b7f69dee2d","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:39:56.957Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/evaluator-super-agent.md","oldString":"- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — context engineering technique relevant to team-specific overlays","newString":"- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — context engineering technique relevant to team-specific overlays\n- [Prompt Engineering Best Practices](prompt-engineering-best-practices.md) — sequential prompting and format-controlled output underpin the 3-phase evaluation pipeline","originalFile":"# Evaluator Super Agent\n\nEvan's primary assignment: build an evaluation agent that automates prototype quality assessment within the [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) pipeline.\n\n**Status: Shipped.** The evaluator is a 3-phase skill pipeline on branch `evan/prototype-evaluate` at [andybraren/prototype-creator](https://github.com/andybraren/prototype-creator). It has evaluated 18+ STRATs against Jira acceptance criteria with Playwright persona walkthroughs.\n\n## What It Does (current)\n\n| Capability | Source | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| AC evaluation | Custom Playwright persona journeys against Jira criteria | Shipped |\n| Usability scoring | 7-dimension rubric with persona overlays (Zack Bodnar's framework) | Shipped |\n| Consistency checking | Beau Morley's consistency checker (source + visual mode) | Shipped |\n| Navigation reachability | Playwright verifies pages are clickable from sidebar | Shipped |\n| Human review | Review tab in HTML report with override buttons + CSV writeback | Shipped |\n| Report hosting | GitLab Pages (eval-reports-7ebc0e.pages.redhat.com) | Shipped |\n| Google Sheet sync | Automated pass/fail + usability metrics to tracking sheet | Shipped |\n| Feedback loop | Eval results → prototype-refine → re-eval (max 3 iterations) | In progress |\n\n## Architecture (confirmed June 16 with Andy)\n\nEvolved from \"single monolithic super agent\" to a **phased pipeline with overlays**:\n\n```\nPhase 1: prototype-evaluate (extract ACs, RFE, Outcome, personas, journeys)\n    ↓ writes extract-state.json\nPhase 2: evaluate-journey (Playwright walkthroughs, consistency check)\n    ↓ writes journey-log.json, screenshots, CSV\nPhase 3: evaluate-usability (7-dimension persona scoring)\n    ↓ updates journey-log.json\nPhase 4: render-report.js + sync-sheet.js (HTML, CSV, Google Sheet)\n```\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n1. **Outcomes over Strategic Goals** as grounding criteria (Outcomes are consistently written)\n2. **One Playwright pass** — shared screenshots across usability, consistency, and AC checks\n3. **98% generic + 2% product overlay** (`config/product-overlay.yaml`) — portable to other products\n4. **Hint mechanism** for dead-end navigation (failure logged but journey continues)\n5. **Human-in-the-loop** — Review tab for designer input before feedback loop acts\n\n## Research References\n\n- **Avenir-UX** — autonomous UX evaluation agent using SEQ/SUS + persona framework\n- **UXCascade** — multi-agent persona simulation with severity-rated issues (S1–S4)\n- GitLab Notes REST API for MR comment posting\n- Danger bot framework for CI-integrated review automation\n\n## How It Connects\n\n```\nJira STRAT (Outcome → RFE → STRAT)\n    → prototype-create (generates code in workspace)\n    → prototype-evaluate (this agent — 3 phases)\n        ├── Phase 1: Extract ACs, personas, journeys from Jira\n        ├── Phase 2: Playwright journeys + consistency check\n        ├── Phase 3: Usability dimension scoring\n        └── Phase 4: Report + Sheet sync\n    → Human reviews report (override verdicts, add notes)\n    → prototype-refine (acts on suggestions + human annotations)\n    → Re-evaluate (loop until PASS or max iterations)\n    → prototype-submit (MR to GitLab)\n```\n\n## Key Design Inputs from Demo (May 14)\n\nFrom the [Prototype Creator Demo](prototype-creator-demo-may14.md):\n- Consistency checkers should only evaluate what's NEW (CSS class=\"new\" tagging)\n- Even auto-mode should produce decision-kit pages for post-review\n- Evaluator needs outcome-level awareness, not just feature-level\n- Preview URL is the evaluation entry point (load the MR URL, assess in browser context)\n- Token efficiency matters — scope evaluation to changed areas only\n\n## Related\n\n- [Outcome Tiger Team](outcome-tiger-team.md) — proposes outcome-level awareness for evaluation, directly extending this agent's scope\n- [Prototype Creator Demo — May 14](prototype-creator-demo-may14.md) — walkthrough with design insights for this agent\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — the pipeline this plugs into\n- [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md) — existing scoring to extend\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — pattern for automated eval loops\n- [Decision Kit](decision-kit.md) — using /strategize to plan this agent\n- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — informs methodology choice\n- [My Cursor Claw](my-cursor-claw.md) — the workspace where this will be built\n- [Ansible AI Helpers Strategy — 2026-06-17](ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md) — heuristic eval pilot connects to automated evaluation vision\n\n## Updates from June 16, 2026 Review\n\nDecisions made with Andy Braren (see [Andy/Evan Eval Review — June 16](andy-evan-eval-review-2026-06-16.md)):\n\n- **Architecture confirmed:** Centralized super evaluator, not fragmented skills. One Playwright pass, shared screenshots.\n- **Grounding confirmed:** Outcomes as primary criteria, Strategic Goals excluded for now.\n- **Overlay approach adopted:** 98% generic + 2% product-specific layer. See [GitLab skill-overlays best practice](https://gitlab.cee.redhat.com/global-engineering/wg-agentic-sdlc/-/blob/main/best-practices/skill-overlays.md).\n- **Hint mechanism shipped:** Simulated UX researcher provides next URL on failure, allowing evaluation to continue while logging failure impact.\n- **Screenshot consolidation:** Sub-agents share one set of Playwright screenshots instead of each capturing independently.\n\n- [RH AI-First UX — 2026-06-18](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-18.md) — Evan demoed automated usability testing + PatternFly consistency checker to full team\n- [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 22](andy-evan-2026-06-22.md) — eval iteration history, flagging system, Prototype Creator integration strategy\n- [AI-First Sync — June 25](ai-first-sync-2026-06-25.md) — Evan's full evaluator presentation to the team, readiness check discussion\n- [RH AI-First UX — June 25](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-25.md) — testing fragmentation concerns, unified testing proposal\n- [Standup — June 29](standup-2026-06-29.md) — 2 automated usability testing agents in development\n- [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — context engineering technique relevant to team-specific overlays\n- [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 29](andy-evan-2026-06-29.md) — findings tab, auto-fix vs report-only modes, X-ray vs blind evaluation, centralized dashboard\n- [Midpoint Check-in — June 30](midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md) — Zack: \"pioneering work\" combining research + AI + SDLC; report must be immediately actionable for designers\n- [Weekly Design Sync — July 1](weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md) — Evan to demo evaluator next week; Nielsen's heuristics confirmed as base rubric\n\n## Sources\n\n- [Andy/Evan Eval Review — June 16](andy-evan-eval-review-2026-06-16.md)\n- Andy/Evan meeting notes — 2026-06-08\n- sources/2026-06-09-prototype-creator-overview.html\n- /strategize session — 2026-06-09 (in progress)\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":98,"oldLines":6,"newStart":98,"newLines":7,"lines":[" - [RH AI-First UX — June 25](rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-25.md) — testing fragmentation concerns, unified testing proposal"," - [Standup — June 29](standup-2026-06-29.md) — 2 automated usability testing agents in development"," - [Skill Overlays](skill-overlays.md) — context engineering technique relevant to team-specific overlays","+- [Prompt Engineering Best Practices](prompt-engineering-best-practices.md) — sequential prompting and format-controlled output underpin the 3-phase evaluation pipeline"," - [Andy/Evan Meeting — June 29](andy-evan-2026-06-29.md) — findings tab, auto-fix vs report-only modes, X-ray vs blind evaluation, centralized dashboard"," - [Midpoint Check-in — June 30](midpoint-checkin-2026-06-30.md) — Zack: \"pioneering work\" combining research + AI + SDLC; report must be immediately actionable for designers"," - [Weekly Design Sync — July 1](weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md) — Evan to demo evaluator next week; Nielsen's heuristics confirmed as base rubric"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
